29/10/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Finance Minister Milen Velchev signed a financing memorandum on Bulgaria's PHARE National Programme 2003 with the European Commission on Tuesday (28 October). Bulgaria will receive a grant of 94.9m euros, of which 47.4m will go towards institutional building projects. The rest will be spent on investment projects.
In other news, Chief of General Staff of the Bulgarian Army General Nikola Kolev left Wednesday for Serbia-Montenegro, where he will discuss bilateral military co-operation with his Serbia-Montenegro counterpart, Colonel General Branko Krga. (Trud, 24 Chassa, Dnevnik, BNNews - 29/10/03; BTA, BNT - 28/10/03)
